data.title: 输出什么?
data.desc:
```javascript
// 🎉✨ This is my 100th question! ✨🎉

const output = `${[] && 'Im'}possible!
You should${'' && `n't`} see a therapist after so much JavaScript lol`
```
data.options: {"options":["possible! You should see a therapist after so much JavaScript lol","Impossible! You should see a therapist after so much JavaScript lol","possible! You shouldn't see a therapist after so much JavaScript lol","Impossible! You shouldn't see a therapist after so much JavaScript lol"],"isMulti":false,"answer":[1]}
data.explanation:
`[]`是一个真值。 使用`&&`运算符，如果左侧值是真值，则返回右侧值。 在这种情况下，左侧值`[]`是一个真值，所以返回`Im`。
`""`是一个假值。 如果左侧值是假的，则不返回任何内容。 `n't`不会被退回。
